            <sentence id="2.3">One is that Firefox crash and close.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">The other one is that the film and the upper part of the tabs appear twice and the font of the menus changes.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">I tried to make a screen capture but it said that the memory was full because of too many applications while actually less than a fourth of the memory was used.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Sometimes</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Go to http://firefoxflicks.com/</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2a. Open several (10-12) movies in separated tabs</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3 Watch whem and it will probably crash</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">2b.It seems that it occurs too if one opens the film one by one (watching it and closing it before opening the next one)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">I got that bug with both FF 1.5.0.2 and Bon Echo 2.0a1 and I am using QuickTime 7.0.3</sentence>
